description.3: The 4/23rd participates in their deadliest mission yet!
description.4: Mary Jane Watson's life is in turmoil- and Peter Parker is the cause! While Mary Jane tries to sort out what she will do next, Spider-Man finds himself face-to-face with a deadly new Spider-Slayer!
description.5: Revenge of the Gods! Namor is captured by Neptune, God of the Sea. After being spirited to the depths of Hades, Namor is saved by a mysterious stranger and is led to the Fortress of Tartarus.
description.6: After the Federal Government's "Commission" demands that Captain America become an official entity of the U.S. Government, Captain America reflects on whether or not he should accept these conditions. What path will Cap choose? The hero? Or the politician?
description.7: The New Mutants attend a party hosted by the Hellfire Club! As if tensions weren't already high enough, Selene drops a bomb on Magma during the soiree…
description.8: Starbrand takes a trip to Switzerland. But instead of fun, he finds danger- not only for himself, but for his friends as well!
description.9: Silver Surfer rises in his own ongoing! Bound to Earth, Surfer makes the most of his situation. Will the being who once was Norrin Radd understand humanness once more? Surfer agrees to some unsavory terms with Galactus -- all to reclaim his freedom!
description.10: While the West Coast Avengers battle through Space-Time, Dr. Strange and The Fantastic Four protect the present!
description.13: Randy cannot tell what is real and what is dream inside the Clinic!
description.14: Storm, Mistress of the elements, claims the spotlight in "Hope"!
description.15: Wayne Tucker will have to face his biggest enemy yet -- his own mind. Will his teammates step up to help him?
description.17: Banner has made an important discovery about his transformation into the Hulk. So what does he do with this new information? Well, he goes drinking...
description.18: Just when Tony thought he had enough trouble with the Ghost, Spymaster enters the battle swearing revenge.
description.19: Thor has fallen in battle...or has he? Though his body lies broken, his Asgardian spirit remains! But can even his soul survive against the inexorable march of the Destroyer?
description.23: The FF have their hands full when Alicia Masters is captured by a raving mad Quicksilver! How can they possibly defeat what they can't catch? And introducing the new leader of the Fantastic Four- Ben Grimm!?
description.24: Having been left out of the loop for some time, Alex Summers finds out that he has a lot to catching up to do, especially when it comes to the Hellfire Club and the Morlocks!
description.25: Silver Sable sics her men on Spidey! With a special appearance by Daredevil, Man Without Fear!
description.26: With the menace of the Hobgoblin finished, Spider-Man's life is back on track. Not even the Preserver can ruin Spidey's renewed dedication to be Spider-Man. But what of the wall-crawler's alter-ego, Peter Parker? His life now seems more meaningless than ever!
description.27: Following Hercules' disappearance, the team investigates. Fearing the worst, Thor goes up to Olympus to alert Hercules' family. There, Thor does battle with the Greco-Roman gods, who blame the Mighty Thunderer and the Avengers for Hercules' interest in Earth.
description.28: Is Captain America obsolete? In the final chapter of the Power Broker Saga, the U.S. Army claims he is and to replace him they've created the ultimate super soldier- G.I. Max!
description.36: The men encounter an unexpected enemy in the bowels of a Viet Cong tunnel system.
description.38: Paste Pot Peep derides Peter and Mary Jane's restaurant night! Captain Americat guest stars!
description.39: Magik gives Magneto a tour of Limbo after he scolds the New Mutants.
description.41: The bounty hunters make their move. Will any of the D.P.7 escape?
description.42: A deadly game of tag ensues between Wolverine and Sabretooth in ""Tag, Sucker!""
description.43: Stalker has the ability to drain the life force from anyone who may stand in his way. For perhaps the first time, Psi-Force is ill equipped for this encounter!
description.44: Daredevil investigates a new drug on the streets of New York that uses Voodoo as a gimmick but the Man Without Fear is about to come face-to-face with someone who truly knows the mysterious ways of Voodoo.
description.45: As a Hulkbuster is about to deliver the final blow to Rick Jones, someone steps in to save him!
description.46: How do you fight a ghost? Iron Man faces that very real problem when a villain called the Ghost starts some destructive haunting of Stark Enterprises.
description.47: Ragnarok on Earth! Thor clashes with his ultimate enemy, his destined demise, the World Serpent Jormungand! But when the smoke clears, will either combatant be left standing?
description.51: The Thing gets lovesick! When Ben Grimm gets the opportunity to travel to the past and marry his old love Alicia, he jumps at the chance! But can he go through with it knowing that he'd be living a lie?
description.52: Dazzler: BURIED ALIVE! Plus, another round with Juggernaut. Only this time, Dazzler's got backup!
description.56: The rise of Hobgoblin! One of Spidey's most elusive villains is revealed in this shocking issue! Friends and family mourn the loss of Ned Leeds- how is Betty Brant handling her grief?
description.57: An Edwin Jarvis-centric issue! Jarvis reflects on his years of service for the Avengers, and decides to return to the Mansion despite injuries inflicted by past villains.
description.58: Guest-starring, The Brothers Grimm! The Needle! Tatterdemalion! Gypsy Moth! Shroud! Danse Macabre! Night Shift! Digger! Werewolf! Canaan! Where's Captain America in all this? He's right in the middle of a climactic battle with the Power Broker!
description.67: The CONCLUSION to Fantastic Four Vs. The X-Men! The FF join the X-Men crew in their efforts to heal Shadowcat of her molecular dispersion.
description.68: Ed Marks takes center stage in this emotional issue.
description.69: Professor Xavier is completely conflicted when he learns the truth behind the Mutant Massacre!
description.70: Will the West Coast Avengers fall prey to the ravages of their travel through the past?
description.73: One of the D.P.7 has been apprehended! Who has been captured?!
description.74: Nightcrawler finds solace from a stranger in ""The Gift!""
description.75: Can our teenaged psychic heroes stop a womanizing beast who is running amok?
description.76: When a down-on-luck worker accidently kills his boss, a movement against the wealthiest New Yorkers grows, but when the movement becomes too big to handle, can Daredevil intervene to keep everyone safe?
description.77: While the Hulkbusters are trying to capture and kill Rick Jones, Clay Quartermain calls in a special request to the morgue.
description.78: Iron Man unveils his special deep sea armor for a government mission to stop enemy forces from opening an old toxic gas tank in the wreckage of the Titanic.
description.79: The Star Brand is at stake! The Old Man demands Ken Connell return the brand to him or he will KILL DEBBIE! How can Ken make such an impossible choice?
description.80: A disguised Thor faces off with Fin Fang Foom in Manhattan! But things are not as they seem with either combatant, as Fin Fang Foom reveals himself to be the World Serpent, Jormungand! Too bad for him that the Serpent's deadliest fear just so happens to be--the might God of Thunder himself!
description.84: Johnny and Alicia's honeymoon is interrupted when people start mysteriously disappearing without a trace! It seems even vacation can't keep the Torch out of the game for long, as he goes head-to-head with Project: Survival!
description.85: Dazzler versus the Juggernaut! Plus, a train session with the X-Men and Callisto!
description.89: Sgt. Little leads the men out on a Paul Revere mission, but not everyone will make it back.
description.90: Following a rejection from Batty Brant, Peter treats himself by attending a 'celebrity' party…where the Hobgobbler attacks!
description.95: GANG WAR CONCLUSION Has the battle been won? Kingpin returns to being the crime lord of New York, but Spider-Man and Daredevil still want words with him. Betty makes a horrifying discovery about Hobgoblin's identity!
description.96: Doctor Druid decides to join the Avengers! Following Wasp's departure, Captain America offers young Captain Marvel the position of chairwoman. After deliberating amongst herself and her family, Captain Marvel accepts!
description.97: Captain America's investigation into the illegal body-building techniques used by the Super-Patriot may spell Cap's doom. Plus: premiering the hardest-working henchmen ever- the Sweat Shop!
description.99: Magik narrowly escapes the infected wrath of S'ym!

2.text: With little progress in humanity's battle against the alien horde, a member of Strikeforce Morituri discovers that their enemies may have a cure for the Morituri process! Will this discovery change the loyalty of the team forever?

7.text: The New Mutants attend a party hosted by the Hellfire Club! As if tensions weren't already high enough, Selene drops a bomb on Magma during the soiree…

21.text: Tension between Jean Grey and Scott Summers comes to its breaking point when Scott discovers that Jean, Phoenix and Madelyne are one in the same woman!

29.text: The Fallen Angels are completely outmatched by giant dinosaurs on the Forest Planet, but two mysterious heroes come and save the day…Moon Boy and Devil Dinosaur!

30.text: After skirmishes with the Fantastic Four, the X-Factor and the X-Men, Mephisto turns his attention to a new foe: the Avengers.

31.text: Punisher's one man war on crime ramps us as he turns his focus to the drug trade!

32.text: Lucian and Lita gain shocking insight into Keith when his sister shares his nightmares with them. Who is the mystery woman that’s been plaguing Nightmask?

34.text: When faced with a difficult decision, the inventor of the Morituri process must choose between obeying the government or his conscience. His decision may ultimately affect the Strikeforce in ways they have yet to imagine!

35.text: Magneto has come before the World Court! And the verdict is...

37.text: It's Ewok vs Ewok! What force has put brother against brother?

39.text: Magik gives Magneto a tour of Limbo after he scolds the New Mutants.

49.text: Iceman’s control over his powers continue to slip to devastating effect.

55.text: The Brainstorm Computer is gone… and so is Top Dog! Which thief belongs to this dastardly deed?

59.text: It's the conclusion - Star Wars According to the Droids, Book III!

60.text: Hank Pym returns to doing what he does best- being one of Earth's Mightiest heroes! After years of failure and personal loss, Hank Pym rebounds stronger than ever. But will the former Ant-Man become a full-fledged member of the West Coast Avengers? Plus, the never-boring Moon Knight flirts with the possibility of becoming a hero. Could this be Moon Knight’s chance at redemption?

61.text: Warlock, Sunspot, and Multiple Man walk into a restaurant…but find themselves in the Beat Street Club instead!

62.text: Mr. Fantastic warns the X-Men of Mephisto's soul-stealing rampage. Rogue has a plan to stop him, but does it play right into his hands?

63.text: Keith relives his own nightmares when he enters the dreams of a boy who’s older brother was killed by the vigilante, Justice.

65.text: The Alien Horde continues to lay waste to Los Angeles! With very little of chance of survival, the Morituri team launch a desperate attack to fight off their enemies. Will humanity be able to survive this galactic attack?

66.text: What unfinished business does Magneto have in Singapore? And how far will the X-Men go to support him in his enigmatic quest? Will they truly stand against the Earth's Mightiest?

69.text: Professor Xavier is completely conflicted when he learns the truth behind the Mutant Massacre!

70.text: Will the West Coast Avengers fall prey to the ravages of their travel through the past?

82.text: X-Factor charge Skids may return to the Morlocks unless Rusty can convince her otherwise.

87.text: What will become of the first generation of Morituri champions of Mankind now that the even more amazing second generation of super-powered human warriors are ready for battle?

88.text: While a group of Soviet heroes, hell-bent on revenge against Magneto, battle the Avengers, who want to try Magneto for his crimes, the X-Men slip away with the hypnotized Master of Magnetism. Where they go, will the Avengers follow?

91.text: Sunspot has fully committed to being evil, taking on his first criminal act in a way you won't believe!

92.text: Mr. Fantastic enlists the aid of X-Factor in order to rescue Sue's soul from Mephisto!

93.text: An illiterate teenager who’s getting involved with a gang is convinced to turn his life around after a visit from Nightmask.

98.text: Will the Ewoks escape the Black Cavern?

99.text: Magik narrowly escapes the infected wrath of S'ym!
